However, here we still have something missing - the virtual operator, which would force those to be cheaper.
Probably won't be long to arrive.
That Czech operators are part of the most expensive in Europe, we have already written it on mobile.cz.
The rest also confirmed this by the Czech Telecommunications Office (ČTU) which warned that the price of SMS messages in our country is of the most expensive in the Union.
After the last steps of the European Commission in the field of the regulation of roaming rates it is likely to come to a paradoxical situation - for some customers of Czech mobile operators the SMS they send from abroad will be cheaper than if they send them from home.
How can prices in the Czech Republic remain so high compared to Europe?
The answer is simple, lack of competition that really wants to fight.
This probably seems paradoxical to us because we have three mobile networks and their high coverage is more than 100%.
On the contrary, mobile operators like to complain that there is extreme competition in the Czech market.
The President of the Council of the Czech Telecommunications Office (ČTU), Pavel Dvořák, said that there is no longer any place in the Czech Republic for any other operator.
It is perhaps true that for a classic operator with their own network no longer has too many possibilities (for the rest, it would be very difficult to find some frequency).
However, there is still a possibility - the virtual operator.
Precisely the entrance of the virtual operator to the mobile phone market brought a marked decrease in prices to which the classic operators should also react.
At the same time, even before the entrance of sharks such as Tesco Mobile or Virgin Mobile to the market in Britain, similar voices were heard there as well as here.
It has been shown that there is a place for such operators and that they can be successful.
On the other hand, there is no need to look for examples too far.
