Only after half a year did this operator get more than 100,000 customers and become the fifth largest operator in the neighbouring country.
On the other hand, after Mobilking there is the Penta group which, apart from that, in the Czech Republic is the owner of U:fon.
The advantage of virtual operators is the ability to focus on many more specific target groups.
In addition, in order to be able to function effectively, they have many fewer customers than a classic operator.
They do not carry relatively large costs in the construction, operation and maintenance of the network.
In the world these types of virtual operators are usually low-cost - they offer cheap SMS calls and messages that, however, are often countered with the offer of more adjusted services.
Thus, for example, Tesco mobile in Britain offers SMS at least half of the cost in relation to competition.
