The service, until the afternoon, was used by more than four hundred people.
Those who start using the internet as a form of trade, can definitely start to forget about ticket sales in the subway stations, where so far they had to queue regularly to take out a normal ticket.
The bonus is purchased online, and the Opencard card recharges it to one of the thirteen subsidiaries of the Municipal Library.
“In these places there is a window with trained personnel available to passengers that helps those interested with internet shopping and also with the charge of the bonus purchased on their card,” said the project spokesman Martin Opatrný.
Apart from the library, it will also be possible to recharge the electronic bonus on the Opencard on the vending machines found in some lobbys of the subway.
What are these vending machines like?
