The bonus is controlled by the machine instead of the driver
The use of the machine, which will start working tomorrow, is simple.
Just enter the Opencard chip card into it and the previously paid bonus will only be charged on it.
Electronic bonds from tomorrow are valid not only in the capital but also in its surroundings.
That is to say, in the surrounding trains and bus lines from the numbers 300 to 499 that mainly use the inhabitants of the central Bohemian localities.
“On the trains attached to the integrated transport of Prague there are reviewers equipped with a reader card that will help confirm the validity of the time and the bonus zone,” explained Filip Drápal of the Ropid organization, which establishes the schedules of the collective transport of Prague.
The surrounding buses have their reader cards mounted in the driver's locker.
Upon entering it is necessary not only to show the card to the driver but also to accompany it with the Opencard at the place intended for it on the side of the Box.
With this, the driver controls the validity of the bond.
“If the passenger needs to verify the validity of the bonds there is nothing easier than requesting this information from the driver,” Drápal said.
Passengers who do not travel on encircling buses and do not remember when they are finished the validity of the bond can address the vending machines where the cards are recharged.
