Psychology of overlapping: Why do we spend more money?
The auction participants are likely to spend more money and overestimate the product.
New York University neurologists and economists discovered the neurological - economical bases of this known and seemingly irrational behavior.
According to the study in Science magazine, people do not want to lose in skills such as eBay auctions, so they prefer to pay even an excessive price.
Scientists tried to establish the neurological scheme of this game by experimental auctions.
One volunteer group played lottery, the other participated in an auction and meanwhile was examined through the functional magnetic resonance system (fMRI) the active brain areas of the people participating in the experiment.
In both games the participants could earn money, but during auctions, where it is fundamental to bet more than the other, losing the game intensified the operation of the complex called stratum located below the cerebral cortex.
This area of the brain, in addition to many other functions, plays a role in the mechanism of self prize of the nervous system.
According to scientists, the increase in betting is explained as a prevention not to cause an intense reaction of the stratum.
To substantiate their theory, the economists of the scientific group also conducted a financial follow-up study.
In this experiment three groups fought against a person in different circumstances.
The control group was simply informed of the actual value of the product in question, and its members bet.
Another group was also promised that if they won, they would receive $15 more.
On the other hand, the third group received exactly $15 prior to the auction, but in case the auction was lost, the members of the group lost even that money.
Thus the only difference between the two groups was that for one the triumph was highlighted and for the other the failure.
However, by checking the hypothesis of the neurologists, the members of the group that played - against failure - were willing to bet even more than the members of the control group and the group - the winner -
These results cannot be deduced from any previously existing economic theory.
For those so far explained the phenomena of auctions only with the joy of winning and with the prevention of risks.
Only visual neurological methods helped to resolve this contradiction between the two theories, so that we now come to a third explanation - Andrew Schotter, professor of the economics faculty of the University of New York.
Hepatitis: When should you go to the doctor?
In the world some 500 million people suffer from chronic hepatitis B or C, and in Hungary chronic liver disease is considered one of the main causes of death.
The number of people infected in this country is estimated at 100,000, but only seven thousand are treated because many of the patients do not know that they are infected.
Hepatitis is the common name for different liver diseases caused by viruses.
Symptoms are very similar; liver infection and jaundice are characteristic, but their pathogens and diseases are very different.
Hepatitis viruses dependent on the pathogen are propagated by two main forms: hepatitis A and E through food (e.g. with water or contaminated food), hepatitis B, C, D and other viruses with blood and body moods (sperma, vaginal mood, saliva).
Travelers are recommended to be protected by A and B vaccines, against C there are no vaccines.
Symptoms of hepatitis A appear two or three weeks after consuming the infected food, it manifests through a general condition, weakness, abdominal pain and nausea.
After this appear in the skin and in the white of the eyes jaundice, the excrement becomes clear, the dark-colored urine and healing can last even two - three weeks.
Every year a million people die worldwide in cancer and liver cirrhosis caused by hepatitis B, the most serious forms of this disease.
The main reason for this is that according to the calculations, only one in ten infected patients receive pharmacological treatment.
Hepatitis C can also have very serious consequences: without treatment it can produce liver cirrhosis and even cancer.
Most people who are infected do not know that they are sick because this pathological agent gradually destroys liver cells and often the first symptoms appear only 20-30 years later.
Therefore, premature recognition, systematic medical control, is very important.
This disease is much more common in three groups: people who had blood transfusions before 1991, drug users and tattooers.
There are currently about 200 million people in the world suffering from chronic hepatitis C.
As this disease can be discovered with routine laboratory control too, it is worth consulting with the family doctor when experiencing some unknown symptoms.
The disease is cured if it is discovered on time, it is possible to exterminate the virus from the body, so you can suppress the infection and prevent cancer.
September 30 is the World Hepatitis Day, which was first organized in 2004 by organizations representing the sick.
Its objective is to draw attention to the causes of chronic liver infections caused by viruses and to the importance of their premature recognition.
Does it hurt less who believe in God?
According to the result of a recent investigation, religious faith has a soothing effect that also alleviates the death of the martyrs of Catholicism.
The Oxford University scientists conducted an interesting experiment: they analyzed that religious belief in how it influences human pain - the British Telegraph reported.
Within the framework of this unique experiment, 12 Catholic believers and the same number of atheists applied electric shock, while everyone was looking at a painting of the Virgin Mary.
According to the results, Catholic believers were able to exclude most of their pain.
Thanks to the scanning technique of the human brain, it was verified that Catholic believers were able to activate that part of their brain that is responsible for the regulation of pain.
This experiment is the first of the series of research in which scientists, philosophers and theologians from different departments of the University also participate alongside academics.
The analysis occurred as follows; they set a sparking instrument to the patient's left hand, which applied the electrical shock.
The researchers asked the participants of the experiment to look at two paintings; the Virgin Mary, the 17th century work of Sassoferrato and the Lady of the Army of Leonardo da Vinci of the 15th century.
The researchers hoped that the Virgin Mary's spectacle would cause a certain religious spirit among the faithful, while they chose Leonardo's oil because it was not too different from the other, and they thought it had reassuring effect.
Patients spent half an hour in an MRI scanner, receiving 20 electrical shocks in four successive parts during that period while observing the painting of religious theme or the other.
Catholics claimed that when they looked at the Virgin Mary, they felt in security, as individuals, protected, calmed and peace reigned in their hearts.
As they looked at the religious theme picture, they felt about 12 percent less pain than when they looked at Leonardo's work.
Psychologist Miguel Farias who also participated in the experiment, thinks that with any such striking image you can achieve a similar effect with atheists as well, only the proper image must be found.
\"We should find the portrait of a person for whom they feel very positively, as by a mother or a father,\" said the psychologist.
Anglican Bishop Tom Wright celebrated the result of the investigation.
“The exercise of faith should and in many cases really change our personality,” Wright added.
After these formidable results there is only one question: what effect would the regulation of pain have if the faithful were shown to the Madonna de Leonardo or another painter of his size?
Would the vision of a high-quality Virgin Mary yield even better results?
